The paper discusses the use of neural networks for learning generalised policies for planning problems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on Action Schema Networks (ASNets), which are a type of neural network architecture designed for planning problems, indicating that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL). The evaluation of ASNets on probabilistic and deterministic domains suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO) or systems and control (cs.SY).
